cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on predicting sememes, which are the minimum semantic units of human languages. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a model for this task, which involves machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses dictionary definitions to predict sememes, which involves understanding the meaning of words, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper also evaluates its model on a knowledge base, which involves information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on predicting sememes could also be relevant to neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
